The Blade A601 presents maturation for ZTE in many areas, especially the need to stay connected with long battery life which doubles as a Powerbank with its OTG reverse charging function to charge other compatible devices.The phone has impressed me with its awesome super large 4000mAh battery capacity that offers a life of one day of heavy usage while on light use, users can receive an impressive 2-3 days battery life.The Blade A601 features a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with HD (720 x 1280 pixels) resolution that is rated to deliver a pixel density of 294ppi which is great for a mid-range phone.What also makes this phone impressive and a stand out is its slick rounded side edges, the phone runs on Android 6.0 with 1GB of RAM and 8GB ROM 13 megapixel camera, all the smart features you need in a phone with a longer battery life.These days, an impressive phone is one with a good camera. People would literally buy a phone for its camera and ZTE is game with its camera front.The Blade A601 flaunts an 8-megapixel primary autofocus camera with LED flash and various camera features including continuous shutter, digital zoom, geo-tagging, panorama, HDR, photo touch, face detection, white balance, ISO, exposure, timer scene and more.It can also record HD (720p) video at 30fps. There is a 2-megapixel front-facing camera for selfies and video calling.The ZTE Blade A601 runs on Android 5.1 Lollipop and packs in a massive 4000mAh battery which is rated to deliver up to 20 hours of talktime and up to 450 hours of standby time on 3G network.For connectivity, the device includes 4G LTE, 3G, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, A-GPS, USB 2.0, OTG, 3.5mm audio jack and FM radio options. It measures 145 x 71 x 8.2mm and weighs 145g.INDIE BOYCE